This code selects the image element, adds a click event listener, and when clicked, it finds the next sibling element (the dropdown menu) and sets its display property to 'block', making it visible.

3. To hide the dropdown menu when clicked outside, you can add an event listener to the document:
```javascript
document.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
  if (!event.target.closest('.chat-info')) {
    const dropdownMenus = document.querySelectorAll('.dropdown-menu');
    dropdownMenus.forEach((menu) => menu.style.display = 'none');
  }
});
```
This code listens for clicks on the document, and if the target element is not within the `.chat-info` container, it hides all dropdown menus.

